oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: German bank note, 1,000 RM
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The Imperial German eagle decorates the front of this light brown 1,000-mark Reichsbank note. On the backside, the Imperial eagle is flanked by two female personages wearing flowing robes. Capt. William L. Thomas, HQ Bttry., 879th FA BN, 69th Inf. Div. brought the note home from World War II. Stamped in red on the note is serial number Nr7716929M.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
